
[1]management

   MAN'AGEMENT, n. Conduct; administration; manner of treating, directing
   or carrying on; as the management of a family or of a farm; the
   management of state affairs.

   1. Cunning practice; conduct directed by art, design or prudence;
   contrivance.

   Mark with what management their tribes divide.

   2. Practice; transaction; dealing.

   He had great management with ecclesiastics, in the view to be advanced
   to the pontificate.

   3. Modulation; variation.

   All directions as to the management of the voice, must be regarded as
   subsidiary to the expression of feeling.
